string.name: napi_get_property_names_description
string.value: napi_get_property_names is one of the N-API interfaces in Node.js, used to retrieve the names of all enumerable properties of a given object.

string.name: napi_get_property_description
string.value: napi_get_property is an N-API function used to retrieve the value of a specific property of a JavaScript object.

string.name: napi_set_property_description
string.value: napi_set_property is an N-API function used to set properties on a JavaScript object.

string.name: napi_has_property_description
string.value: napi_has_property is an N-API function used to check if a specified property exists in a JavaScript object and its prototype chain.

string.name: napi_delete_property_description
string.value: napi_delete_property is an N-API function used to delete a specified property from a JavaScript object.

string.name: napi_get_named_property_description
string.value: The napi_get_named_property function is used to retrieve the value of a named property from a JavaScript object. It allows you to access the value associated with a specified property name on the given object.

string.name: napi_set_named_property_description
string.value: The napi_set_named_property function is used to set a named property on a JavaScript object. It associates a value with a specified property name on the given object. This function allows you to add or modify properties on an object dynamically during runtime.

string.name: napi_has_named_property_description
string.value: The napi_has_named_property function is used to check if a JavaScript object has a named property. It allows you to determine whether the given object has a specified property name.

string.name: napi_get_element_description
string.value: napi_get_element is a function in Node.js N-API that allows native addons to retrieve an element from a JavaScript array by its index. The function provides a mechanism for native code to access array elements, enabling manipulation or inspection of JavaScript arrays directly from C or C++ code.

string.name: napi_set_element_description
string.value: napi_set_element is a function in the Node.js N-API that allows native addons to set an element in a JavaScript array at a specified index. This function enables native code, written in C or C++, to modify or assign values to elements within JavaScript arrays directly.

string.name: napi_has_element_description
string.value: napi_has_element is a function in Node.js N-API that checks if an element exists at a specified index in a JavaScript array. This function allows native code written in C or C++ to easily query JavaScript arrays to determine the presence of an element at a given index. It facilitates interaction between native plugins and JavaScript arrays, allowing native code to better integrate with and manipulate data within the JavaScript environment.

string.name: napi_delete_element_description
string.value: napi_delete_element is a function in the Node.js N-API that enables the removal of an element at a specified index within a JavaScript array. This function allows native code, written in C or C++, to directly manipulate JavaScript arrays by providing a straightforward mechanism to delete elements.
